NUMBER 2312
NAME Garump Mansion, diamond room
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
This chamber has a high ceiling, unusually high when compared to the corridor
heights. A chandelier hangs there, far out of reach, directly above the massive
wooden table. Only one chair sits by the table, equally heavily constructed.
The room is perfectly square, but its walls run at diagonals to the cardinal
directions of north, west and so on. Each corner has a corridor leading away.
Above the low-ceilinged entrances of the corridors are four inward-facing
gargoylish statues, mounted on the same level as the hanging chandelier.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT ABOVE 2317
EXIT S 2311
EXIT E 2313
EXIT W 2314
EXIT N 2315

ITEM 0 91 ADJ1=189 ADJ2=355
PUT 0 1539 VAL1=1
IFPREVERB READ -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1539
                CLEARVERB
                IFVAR DAN2312 = 0
                        ECHO PLAYER There is very faint writing on the parchment.
                ENDIF
                IFVAR DAN2312 = 1
ECHO PLAYER "I am forced to admit to you, dear reader, that I lied when I invited you
ECHO PLAYER to a pleasant dinner. In truth, you and your companions are now mice in a
ECHO PLAYER very sophisticated game of cat and same. A gentleman of some power has made
ECHO PLAYER a most intriguing wager with me, as to whether you can escape before the
ECHO PLAYER sands of the glass run out, an hour from the time I leave you."
ECHO PLAYER "If you can make your way through the main door by which you entered, I
ECHO PLAYER will lose, for it is my opinion that you will never be able to do so. If
ECHO PLAYER this occurs, I will pay to each of you a sum of one thousand (1,000) gold
ECHO PLAYER crowns for your time and achievement, as well as a larger sum to my
ECHO PLAYER opponent. If you fail, I will have won the bet, and will not pay you
ECHO PLAYER anything. You shall simply be left to wander the passages and rooms of
ECHO PLAYER my mansion until you starve or fall prey to one of the traps."
ECHO PLAYER "My opponent has asked me to include some advice for you, but I am not
ECHO PLAYER going to do so. The great adventurers of Fayd can surely pool their
ECHO PLAYER talents and escape from a simple mansion full of traps, minions and
ECHO PLAYER magical tricks without any help from the landlord. Yes, surely so."%c
ECHO PLAYER                                The parchment is signed,
ECHO PLAYER                                 Oethues Garump
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1537
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER It's stuck to the table.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

