NUMBER 2317
NAME Upper half of diamond
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

EXIT BELOW 2312
DROPLOC 2312

;
;The exit above is 2317, which is simply the top half of the room. Though
;aerial, there's no weather or anything due to the regiondef. Ha ha ha. The
;four gargoylish statues and the chandeleir do nothing interesting in and of
;themselves, but in the mouth of the third gargoyle there is a stone switch.
;Flipping the switch sets DAN2317 to 1 or 0, causing the statues to exhale a
;mist that becomes a real gargoyle below in 2312 if it's 1.
;Other stuff: There's a lever in 2316. Pulling it makes a CLUNK sound
;somewhere nearby.

*DESCRIPTION_START
Now level with the chandelier and the four gargoyle statues, you can touch
the ceiling with little effort. From this vantage point, the table and chair
below look different- you can see that their shapes are a little skewed, as
though whoever made them had no straight-edge or level to work with and
only estimated as they went along. The statues, however, have no such
handicap, leering and ugly but remarkably realistic.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 1249
IFPREVERB LIGHT 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You don't have any means of lighting all those candles. Besides, they are already lit.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB EXTINGUISH 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You don't have any means of extinguishing all those candles. They look too numerous to simply blow out.
ENDIF

