NUMBER 2320
NAME Garump Mansion, library
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
Muted tones of green and brown predominate in this room, a room with shelves
lining every wall- empty shelves, mostly. There are a few loose scraps of
paper and parchment here, part of one book's cover, and a number of over
-turned pieces of furniture. A couch lies against one wall, its back and
cushions ripped open, springs hanging loose like entrails. The mirror which
hangs above the door is broken, unable to reflect on anything
save its own demise.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
        IFITEM 6
                ECHO GROUP A panel on the south wall has been pushed aside to reveal an opening.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


